el asks for a 50 percent down payment to start building your sofa with the remainder due when it is ready to ship.","Other helpful information on the sofa pages include clean measurements from all sides so you can see if it will fit in your apartment. There is also a graph that shows you how firm the cushions are and how relaxed or upright the back of the sofa is. Crate and Barrel also includes a care section outlining how to best care for your custom sofa once it is in your home. This is a good place to learn whether the fabric you are choosing is stain resistant or good for pets or children since the cleaning instructions differ depending on the material.","Customer reviews are helpful and found on the sofa description page. Here, you will see others sofa buying experience and how satisfied they are with their purchase. You also have the option of going into a local Crate and Barrel showroom to sit on the sofas, then buying a custom sofa online.","Unlike several other popular online sofa outlets, this company delivers your custom sofa to your home fully assembled, so you don’t have to worry about putting anything together once it arrives. The delivery service will ensure your sofa is set up where you want it and will remove any packaging material from your home.","Once your sofa is delivered, you have seven days to decide to return the item, which isn’t very long. Other services, such as <a href=\"/joybird-review\">Joybird</a>, give you a full year to return your couch. If you do decide to return your order, shipping and handling charges aren’t refundable, and you’ll be charged a minimum 25 percent restocking fee based on the condition of the sofa when it is returned."]},"id":"3a19f44b-3724-494b-aea2-ad29aeca13d4","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"29d76a4b-b6ae-476d-b1ec-2ac183fc80c1","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Crate and Barrel is a good option for buying a sofa online, especially if you need a smaller, apartment sized couch. Most of t